task.summary: Solved problem 42 (which was previously in partially solved state). Main challenge with Problem 42 was in trying to be smart about how to generate the triangle numbers. I used a lazy method.
Added solutions 43-45. Note: 44 is not solved with a proof of optimality.
Added solutions to 46 and 47. Definitely some good optimisations to do for 47.
Really trivial solution for 48. Performed a quick cleanup to discard anything but the last ten digits.
Added 49 and 50 which were fine. 50 was fairly interesting just with a double for loop.
Problem 51 is quite tricky. I should revisit this to create a more elegant solution.
Really enjoyed coding Problem 54. Not that complex but got to think through all the cases.
